and, for more ironic historical pondering, note &quot;On December 2, 1942 about forty people watched Enrico Fermi and his team set off the first nuclear chain reaction at Chicago Pile-1 in a racquets court under the west stands of the abandoned stadium.&quot;

The abandoned stadium mentioned is the field pictured here (name changed to Stagg Field in 1913).
